components.description: Cloudflare Realtime is infrastructure for real-time audio/video/data applications. It allows you to build real-time apps without worrying about scaling or regions. It can act as a selective forwarding unit (WebRTC SFU), as a fanout delivery system for broadcasting (WebRTC CDN) or anything in between.

components.name: Realtime TURN Service
components.description:
Separately from the SFU, Realtime offers a managed TURN service. TURN acts as a relay point for traffic between WebRTC clients like the browser and SFUs, particularly in scenarios where direct communication is obstructed by NATs or firewalls. TURN maintains an allocation of public IP addresses and ports for each session, ensuring connectivity even in restrictive network environments.

Using Cloudflare Realtime TURN service is available free of charge when used together with the Realtime SFU. Otherwise, it costs $0.05/real-time GB outbound from Cloudflare to the TURN client.

Cloudflare is investigating issues with network performance in Toronto from 13:38-13:47 UTC.

Cloudflare identified and resolved issues with our DNS API service. Customers may have experienced degraded functionality. DNS traffic was unaffected.

Timeline of impact: 10:30 UTC - 12:30 UTC

incidents.name: Cloudflare create IP access rules issue

incident_updates.body: This incident has been resolved.
A fix has been implemented and we are monitoring the results.

Cloudflare is observing issues creating IP access rules. Customers trying to create IP access rules via the dashboard or API may see an error.

This does not affect already existing rules, nor connectivity, security or CDN functionality.

We are currently working on a resolution. More updates to follow shortly.

incidents.name: Connectivity Issues when using Zero Trust Gateway Egress and Network Policies

incident_updates.body: This incident has been resolved.
A fix has been implemented and we are currently monitoring the results.

Cloudflare has identified an issue causing connectivity problems for a subset of Cloudflare One customers when the traffic requires Zero Trust Gateway Egress (specifically with Hostname selector) or Network policies. We are currently working on applying a fix.

incidents.name: Compressible responses from workers sometimes being sent uncompressed

incident_updates.body: This incident has been resolved.

In some circumstances, Cloudflare will return uncompressed HTTP content for responses from Cloudflare workers, even when the "Accept-Encoding" header has been sent. Cloudflare engineering is engaged and rolling out a fix.
